com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common

Class CircularInteger

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.CircularInteger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>

    public class CircularInteger
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>
    A circular integer is an ever cycling integer value from 0 to size - 1
    When the last value (size) is reached, it resets to 0
    Iterating a Circular Integer will result in an infinite loop, as the sequence never ends
